  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN342-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇaiyum tuṟaiyum avai. aricilkiḻār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div> 
    <div xml:id="PN342">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>kāṉak kākkaik kalicciṟa kēykku</l>
<l>mayilaik kaṇṇip peruntōṭ kuṟumaka</l>
<l>ḷēṉōr makaḷko livaḷeṉa vituppuṟ</l>
<l>ṟeṉṉoṭu viṉavum veṉvē ṉeṭuntakai</l>
<l>tirunayat takka paṇpiṉiva ṇalaṉē</l>
<l>porunark kallatu piṟarkkā kātē</l>
<l>paiṅkāṟ kokkiṉ pakuvāyp piḷḷai</l>
<l>meṉcēṟ ṟaṭaikarai mēyntuṇ ṭataṟpi</l>
<l>ṉāra līṉṟa vaiyavi muṭṭai</l>
<l>kūrna liṟaviṉ piḷḷaiyoṭu peṟūun</l>
<l>taṇpaṇaik kiḻavaṉiva ṭantaiyum vēntarum</l>
<l>peṟāa maiyiṟ pēramar ceytaliṟ</l>
<l>kaḻipiṇam piṟaṅkupōr paḻikaḷi ṟerutā</l>
<l>vāṭaka vaikalu muḻakkum</l>
<l>māṭci yavariva ṭaṉṉai mārē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Oh paragon with a victorious spear who asks from me</l>
<l>in haste </l>
<l>“the young woman with large shoulders [and] a Mayilai chaplet</l>
<l>that resembles the luxuriant wing of the forest crow,</l>
<l>  is she another’s daughter?”</l>
<l>Her innocence of a brilliant quality fit to be longed for,</l>
<l>it is for no other than a fighter.</l>
<l>Her father is the lord of the cool fields,</l>
<l>where the child with gaping beak of the green-legged heron</l>
<l>after what it ate when searching the compacted shore in the soft mire</l>
<l>[now] obtains the mustard-seed [small] eggs brought forth by the Āral fish</l>
<l>along with the children of the abundant good crabs,</l>
<l>  and the king,</l>
<l>because, as they don’t obtain [her], they are making a great fight,</l>
<l>her people will have glory</l>
<l>when they ravage [them] daily, as is befitting the sword,</l>
<l>with elephants as bulls that destroy glistening stacks of passed away corpses.</l>
</lg>
